Release:

- 4.7.0
    - API:
        - Using PostgreSQL instead of MySQL database
        - Docker environments for test, development and production, using docker-compose for the first two

- 4.6.0
    - Web client:
        - Net worth editor (MVP)

- 4.1.0
    - Web client:
        - Now using SVG instead of HTML5 canvas for graphs
        - Automatic insertion of probable category after selection of suggestions during data insert

- 4.0.2
    - All:
        - Many minor fixes
        - Some major fixes
    - API:
        - Now using knex for database migrations and ORM
        - Now using luxon for date manipulation
        - Now using joi for data validation
        - Now using winston for logging
        - Added indexes and utf8mb4 encoding to database
        - Updated authentication logic to use passport with JWTs instead of ad-hoc solution
    - Web client:
        - Increased test coverage and refactors of many components
        - Updated data structures
        - Savings targets
        - Tweaked overview table display format

- 3.2.3
    - Web client:
        - Bug fixes and dev env improvements

- 3.2.2-beta
    - Web client:
        - Saved income on analysis page

- 3.2.1-beta
    - Web client:
        - Timeline on analysis page
        - Bug fixes

- 3.2.0-beta
    - Web client:
        - Use redux-saga for side effects
        - Hot module replacement
        - Refactor reducer and action filenames

- 3.1.8-beta
    - Web client:
        - Better handling of tension in Hermite spline graphs

- 3.1.7-beta
    - CLI client:
        - Made it work with the new API (there are still fatal bugs)
    - API:
        - don't fail tests if scraper test files don't exist

- 3.1.6-beta
    - Web client:
        - Bug fixes
        - Dark, better-formatted stocks list

- 3.1.5-beta
    - Web client:
        - Fixed stock price graph using Yahoo YQL

- 3.1.4-beta
    - Web client:
        - Better support for mobile on the analysis page
        - Revamped cash flow graph

- 3.1.3-beta
    - Web client:
        - Colours on analysis list, plus better layout (using flexbox)

- 3.1.2-beta
    - Web client:
        - Use exponential averages instead of simple medians on the future spending predictions

- 3.1.1-beta-1
    - Web client:
        - Use a custom PureComponent implementation adapted from https://www.npmjs.com/package/react-immutable-pure-component
        - Fix performance bugs with components re-rendering when not necessary

- 3.1.0-alpha-1
    - Web client:
        - Use react-redux with react-router instead of flux

- 3.0.1-alpha-1
    - Responsive layout for mobile and tablet

- 3.0.0-alpha-7
    - Added this file
    - Made Android app work with new API
    - Fixed major web app bug where list items weren't sorted correctly

